# Discord Chat Analysis for ğŸ’¬-coders Channel

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily focused on technical issues related to API integration in a project that uses both Anthropic and OpenAI. The main technical discussion centered around solving an error when using Anthropic's API with an MCP server integration. The error "No handler found for delegate type: TEXT_EMBEDDING" occurred when trying to use only the Anthropic API key without OpenAI. Community members provided solutions, explaining that even when using Anthropic as the primary model, an OpenAI API key is still needed for embedding functionality. It was discovered that the OpenAI key doesn't need to be valid for this purpose - it just needs to have some value. Additionally, there were brief mentions of an "elizacloud v2" and someone sharing a project for feedback, though these topics weren't developed further. A user named "jin" mentioned analyzing council priorities and extracting high-priority issues, suggesting they would write a post about the process.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Can we share links here? (asked by ğ˜½ğ˜¼ğ™ğ™ğ™ğ˜¼ğ™‡ğ™„) A: Unanswered
Q: How can I solve the "No handler found for delegate type: TEXT_EMBEDDING" error when using Anthropic with an MCP server? (asked by Andrei Mitrea) A: Add OpenAI key for embedding and place the OpenAI plugin after Anthropic. (answered by sayonara and Stan âš¡)
Q: Do I need a valid OpenAI API key when using Anthropic with MCP server? (asked by Andrei Mitrea) A: The OpenAI key doesn't need to be valid, it just needs to have some value. (answered by Andrei Mitrea)

The messages suggest publishing something across social platforms and mention potential connections with social media influencers who have 5-10M followers. - Kenk shared what appear to be final ERC-8004 contracts on GitHub
- Borko mentioned rotating Anthropic keys and distributing new ones to team members

- R0am suggested creating a version of the slidegen repository that works with Nano banana

The conversation is mostly brief updates and link sharing rather than in-depth technical discussions. There are mentions of tools like Nano banana for image generation and issues with Claude code review, but without detailed technical problem-solving.
